data.content:
Yes — use `Assert.IsInstanceOfType<T>()`, which asserts the type **and** returns the typed instance (MSTest v3+):

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void Create_ReturnsCorrectHandler()
{
    var factory = new HandlerFactory();
    var result = factory.Create("email");

    var handler = Assert.IsInstanceOfType<EmailHandler>(result);
    Assert.AreEqual("email", handler.Type);
}
```

This is better because:
- It produces a clear failure message if the type is wrong (instead of an `InvalidCastException`)
- It combines the null check and type check in one assertion
- No unsafe cast needed
